Wikitext Gotchas

1. `$reveal` cannot fragment HTML structure

`$reveal` renders as a widget node. You CANNOT use it to conditionally open/close HTML tags across boundaries — TW's widget tree doesn't support loose closing/opening tags inside widget bodies.

```
<!-- BROKEN — renders literal </div><div> text -->
<$reveal type="match" state="..." text="split">
<div class="pane">
</$reveal>

<!-- CORRECT — use CSS class toggle -->
<$let layoutClass={{{[[$:/state/layout]get[text]match[split]then[split-class]]}}}>
<div class=<<layoutClass>>>
  <div class="pane-a">...content...</div>
  <div class="pane-b">...content...</div>
</div>
</$let>
```

Key principle: Always keep HTML structure intact within a single widget scope. Use CSS classes to change layout modes.

---

2. `code-body: yes` disables pragma parsing

With `code-body: yes`, TW treats the entire body as literal content — `\import`, `\procedure`, `\function` at the top are NOT parsed as pragmas. They become visible text.

- **Use `code-body: yes`** for tiddlers with NO pragmas (simple templates, pure HTML/wikitext)
- **Omit `code-body: yes`** if the tiddler uses `\import`, `\procedure`, `\function`, or any pragma

Symptom: headings render as literal `!! Title` because a preceding `\import` wasn't consumed as a pragma.

---

3. `<%-- --%>` is NOT a valid comment

TW has NO wikitext comment syntax `<%-- ... --%>`. This renders as literal text. The `<%if%>` / `<%else%>` / `<%endif%>` conditional syntax exists, but there is no comment variant.

```
<!-- BROKEN — renders as visible text -->
<%-- this is not a comment --%>

<!-- CORRECT — use HTML comments -->
<!-- this is a comment -->
```

---

4. Use `$let` instead of nested `$set`

`$let` is more efficient (no tiddler context creation) and supports multiple variables:

```
<!-- Anti-pattern -->
<$set name="a" value="1"><$set name="b" value="2">...</$set></$set>

<!-- Better -->
<$let a="1" b="2">...</$let>
```

`$set` is still needed for: `filter` attribute (computed value), `select` attribute, `tiddler`/`subtiddler` context.

---

5. TW wraps inline wikitext in `<p>` tags

When wikitext content isn't in block mode, TW wraps it in `<p>`. This matters for test comparisons and layout. Use `$mode="block"` on `$transclude` when you need block-level rendering without `<p>` wrappers.

---

6. `<%if%>`/`<%else%>` + `invokeActions` bug

Action widgets inside `<%else%>` branches are NOT reachable by `Widget.invokeActions()`. The else branch is stored in `elseChildren` which `invokeActions` does not traverse.

```
<!-- BROKEN — action in else branch never fires -->
<%if [<condition>]%>
  <$action-log message="true"/>
<%else%>
  <$action-log message="false"/>
<%endif%>

<!-- CORRECT — use $list with emptyMessage -->
<$list filter="[<condition>]" variable="ignore">
  <$action-log message="true"/>
</$list>
<$list filter="[<condition>]" emptyMessage="""<$action-log message="false"/>"""/>
```

Read-only rendering (not actions) works fine with `<%if%>`.
